---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { CookieOptOut } from '../components/CookieOptOut';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy - Michigan Spots"
  description="Privacy Policy for Michigan Spots platform"
>
  <div class="container mx-auto px-4 py-20">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto prose prose-lg">
      <h1 class="font-display text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-ink-primary mb-6">Privacy Policy</h1>

      <p class="text-sm text-ink-faded mb-8">
        <strong>Effective Date:</strong> October 15, 2025<br />
        <strong>Last Updated:</strong> October 15, 2025
      </p>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-ink-primary mb-4">1. Introduction</h2>
        <p class="text-ink-secondary leading-relaxed">
          Cozyartz Media Group ("we," "us," or "our") operates Michigan Spots, a community-powered discovery game. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our Platform. By using Michigan Spots, you consent to the data practices described in this policy.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-ink-primary mb-4">2. Information We Collect</h2>

        <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-ink-primary mb-3">2.1 Information You Provide</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-ink-secondary space-y-2 mb-4">
          <li><strong>Waitlist Signup:</strong> Name, email address, Michigan city, user interest type</li>
          <li><strong>Partnership Applications:</strong> Name, email, organization name, phone number, city, partnership preferences</li>
          <li><strong>User-Generated Content:</strong> Photos, location descriptions, comments, and other content you submit</li>
          <li><strong>Communication:</strong> Messages sent to our support or contact channels</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-ink-primary mb-3">2.2 Information from Reddit</h3>
        <p class="text-ink-secondary leading-relaxed mb-3">When you connect via Reddit, we may receive:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-ink-secondary space-y-2 mb-4">
          <li>Reddit username and user ID</li>
          <li>Profile information you choose to share</li>
          <li>Activity within the r/michiganspots community</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-ink-primary mb-3">2.3 Automatically Collected Information</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-ink-secondary space-y-2 mb-4">
          <li><strong>Device Information:</strong> Browser type, operating system, device identifiers</li>
          <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> Pages visited, features used, time spent on Platform</li>
          <li><strong>Location Data:</strong> Approximate location based on IP address (we do not track precise GPS location without your permission)</li>
          <li><strong>Cookies and Tracking:</strong> See our Cookie Policy for details</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-ink-primary mb-3">2.4 Payment Information</h3>
        <p class="text-ink-secondary leading-relaxed">
          For partnership payments, we use Stripe as our payment processor. We do not store your full credit card information. Stripe collects and processes payment data in accordance with their privacy policy.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-ink-primary mb-4">3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p class="text-ink-secondary leading-relaxed mb-3">We use collected information to:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-ink-secondary space-y-2">
          <li>Operate and maintain the Michigan Spots platform</li>
          <li>Send launch notifications and platform updates to waitlist members</li>
          <li>Process partnership applications and payments</li>
          <li>Facilitate user interactions and community features</li>
          <li>Display leaderboards, badges, and achievements</li>
          <li>Improve and personalize user experience</li>
          <li>Analyze usage patterns and Platform performance</li>
          <li>Prevent fraud, abuse, and security threats</li>
          <li>Comply with legal obligations</li>
          <li>Communicate about challenges, events, and partner promotions</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-ink-primary mb-4">4. How We Share Your Information</h2>

        <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-ink-primary mb-3">4.1 Public Information</h3>
        <p class="text-ink-secondary leading-relaxed mb-3">The following information may be publicly visible:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-ink-secondary space-y-2 mb-4">
          <li>Spots, photos, and descriptions you submit</li>
          <li>Your Reddit username (via Reddit integration)</li>
          <li>Leaderboard rankings and city affiliation</li>
          <li>Badges and achievements earned</li>
          <li>Comments and community interactions</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-ink-primary mb-3">4.2 Third-Party Service Providers</h3>
        <p class="text-ink-secondary leading-relaxed mb-3">We share information with trusted service providers:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-ink-secondary space-y-2 mb-4">
          <li><strong>Cloudflare:</strong> Hosting, database, and infrastructure services</li>
          <li><strong>Stripe:</strong> Payment processing for partnerships</li>
          <li><strong>Reddit:</strong> Platform integration and authentication</li>
          <li><strong>Analytics Services:</strong> Understanding Platform usage and performance</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-ink-primary mb-3">4.3 Partners and Sponsors</h3>
        <p class="text-ink-secondary leading-relaxed">
          We may share aggregated, anonymized data with partners (e.g., "Challenge had 500 participants from 20 cities"). We do not sell personal information to partners or third parties.
        </p>

        <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-ink-primary mb-3">4.4 Legal Requirements</h3>
        <p class="text-ink-secondary leading-relaxed">
          We may disclose information if required by law, court order, or to protect our rights, safety, or property.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-ink-primary mb-4">5. Data Security</h2>
        <p class="text-ink-secondary leading-relaxed mb-3">
          We implement industry-standard security measures to protect your information:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-ink-secondary space-y-2">
          <li>Encryption of data in transit (HTTPS/TLS)</li>
          <li>Secure database storage via Cloudflare D1</li>
          <li>Limited access to personal information by authorized personnel</li>
          <li>Regular security assessments and updates</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-ink-secondary leading-relaxed mt-4">
          However, no method of transmission over the Internet is 100% secure. While we strive to protect your information, we cannot guarantee absolute security.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-ink-primary mb-4">6. Your Privacy Rights</h2>

        <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-ink-primary mb-3">6.1 Access and Correction</h3>
        <p class="text-ink-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
          You have the right to access and update your personal information. Contact us at privacy@michiganspots.com to request access or corrections.
        </p>

        <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-ink-primary mb-3">6.2 Data Deletion</h3>
        <p class="text-ink-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
          You may request deletion of your account and personal data. Note that some information may be retained as required by law or for legitimate business purposes (e.g., financial records, fraud prevention).
        </p>

        <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-ink-primary mb-3">6.3 Marketing Communications</h3>
        <p class="text-ink-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
          You can opt out of marketing emails by clicking "unsubscribe" in any promotional email or contacting us directly.
        </p>

        <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-ink-primary mb-3">6.4 Cookie Management</h3>
        <p class="text-ink-secondary leading-relaxed mb-6">
          You can manage cookie preferences through our cookie consent banner or your browser settings. See our <a href="/cookies" class="text-lakes-blue hover:underline">Cookie Policy</a> for details.
        </p>

        <div class="not-prose mb-8">
          <CookieOptOut client:load />
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-ink-primary mb-4">7. Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p class="text-ink-secondary leading-relaxed">
          Michigan Spots is available to users aged 13 and older. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If we discover we have collected information from a child under 13, we will promptly delete it. If you believe a child under 13 has provided us with personal information, contact us at privacy@michiganspots.com.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-ink-primary mb-4">8. State-Specific Privacy Rights</h2>

        <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-ink-primary mb-3">8.1 California Residents (CCPA/CPRA)</h3>
        <p class="text-ink-secondary leading-relaxed mb-3">California residents have additional rights under the California Consumer Privacy Act:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-ink-secondary space-y-2 mb-4">
          <li>Right to know what personal information is collected</li>
          <li>Right to delete personal information</li>
          <li>Right to opt out of sale of personal information (note: we do not sell personal information)</li>
          <li>Right to non-discrimination for exercising privacy rights</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-ink-primary mb-3">8.2 Michigan Residents</h3>
        <p class="text-ink-secondary leading-relaxed">
          Michigan does not currently have a comprehensive state privacy law. We extend privacy protections to all users regardless of location.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-ink-primary mb-4">9. Data Retention</h2>
        <p class="text-ink-secondary leading-relaxed">
          We retain personal information for as long as necessary to provide services, comply with legal obligations, resolve disputes, and enforce agreements. Waitlist data is retained until platform launch and for marketing purposes. Partnership data is retained per contractual and financial record-keeping requirements.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-ink-primary mb-4">10. International Users</h2>
        <p class="text-ink-secondary leading-relaxed">
          Michigan Spots is operated in the United States and primarily serves Michigan residents. If you access the Platform from outside the U.S., your information will be transferred to and processed in the United States, which may have different data protection laws than your jurisdiction.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-ink-primary mb-4">11. Affiliate Disclosures</h2>
        
        <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-ink-primary mb-3">11.1 Amazon Associates Program</h3>
        <p class="text-ink-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Michigan Spots is a participant in the Amazon Services LLC Associates Program, an affiliate advertising program designed to provide a means for sites to earn advertising fees by advertising and linking to Amazon.com. When you click on Amazon product links on our site and make a purchase, we may earn a small commission at no additional cost to you. This helps us keep Michigan Spots free and continue sharing amazing Michigan adventures.
        </p>
        
        <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-ink-primary mb-3">11.2 Affiliate Relationship Transparency</h3>
        <p class="text-ink-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
          We only recommend products and services that we believe will be valuable to Michigan explorers. Our affiliate relationships do not influence our editorial content or recommendations. All opinions expressed are our own, and we maintain full editorial control over content featuring affiliate links.
        </p>
        
        <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-semibold text-ink-primary mb-3">11.3 How Affiliate Links Work</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-ink-secondary space-y-2 mb-4">
          <li>Affiliate links contain a tracking code (our Associates ID: cozyartz05-20)</li>
          <li>When you purchase through these links within 24 hours, we earn a commission</li>
          <li>You pay the same price - there is no additional cost to you</li>
          <li>We earn commission on the entire order, not just the linked product</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-ink-primary mb-4">12. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
        <p class="text-ink-secondary leading-relaxed">
          We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. Changes will be posted on this page with an updated "Last Updated" date. Material changes will be communicated via email or prominent Platform notice. Your continued use after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-ink-primary mb-4">13. Contact Us</h2>
        <p class="text-ink-secondary leading-relaxed">
          For questions, concerns, or to exercise your privacy rights, contact:<br />
          <strong>Cozyartz Media Group</strong><br />
          Battle Creek, Michigan<br />
          Email: <a href="mailto:privacy@michiganspots.com" class="text-lakes-blue hover:underline">privacy@michiganspots.com</a><br />
          General Inquiries: <a href="mailto:hello@michiganspots.com" class="text-lakes-blue hover:underline">hello@michiganspots.com</a>
        </p>
      </section>

      <div class="border-t-2 border-ink-primary pt-8 mt-12">
        <p class="text-sm text-ink-faded text-center">
          Â© 2025 Cozyartz Media Group. All rights reserved.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .prose {
    max-width: 100%;
  }
  .prose h1, .prose h2, .prose h3 {
    color: inherit;
  }
  .prose ul {
    margin: 1rem 0;
  }
  .prose li {
    margin: 0.5rem 0;
  }
</style>
